

     
      Might Eclipse one day soon make OSes irrelevant? Thought of until now as being a Java-centric initiative, the Eclipse Foundation under its new executive director releases Eclipse 3.0 today, with its ambitious sights firmly set on making it not just an IDE but a language-neutral, universal application integration platform. 'If you have not been following the milestone releases of Eclipse 3.0, it's definitely time to download a copy and get started,' says JDJ's Eclipse Editor, Bill Dudney.  [Resource-Type: Announcement; Category: Eclipse; XRating: 4]
     
    
